text: Emily Elissa Randall (born October 30, 1985) is an American politician and activist who is a U.S. representative for Washington's 6th congressional district since 2025. She was a member of the Washington State Senate from 2019 to 2024."New Washington state legislators headed to Olympia in 2019". MyNorthwest, December 31, 2018. She is a member of the Democratic Party. She is the first queer Latina to serve in the U.S. House of Representatives. ==References== Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Washington Category:LGBT politicians Category:Queer people Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians
